n>&#160;In </span><em>Defining Aggregators,</em><span> Thompson wrote, &#82=
20;The key characteristic of Aggregators is that they own the user relation=
ship.&#8221; If people go to your site to find anything on the internet, yo=
u can tell them where to go. If people open your app to ride, you can tell =
them whose car to get in. Owning the customer relationship lets aggregators=
 commoditize their suppliers and capture more value from each transaction.&=
#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">ChatGPT (and GPT more broadly) takes this a step =
further and completely disintermediates its &#8220;suppliers.&#8221; Google=
