he products that use OpenAI&#8217;s APIs do other things besides just deliv=
ering ChatGPT in a different interface, and they certainly involve some fin=
e-tuning to better address the customer&#8217;s specific needs, but for mos=
t of these products, it really feels like they&#8217;re breaking the Cardin=
al Rule of APIs: don&#8217;t outsource the thing that </span><a href=3D"htt=
